caption: Letena is my favorite restaurant in DC! The food is amazing (as a vegetarian, I adore the veggie sampler, particularly both mushroom dishes) and everyone that works there is so kind. Letena is my go-to place to take friends visiting DC and everyone always loves the food and warm welcome.
Great flavor. Loved their yellow lentil.

Great customer service! A partner and I wanted to experience Ethiopian coffee and accidentally showed up before opening time. They waved us in and kindly made coffee for us. I’m looking forward to trying their food soon!
So good! My favorite is the garlic injera. High quality - already looking forward to the next order.
The absolute best Ethiopian food you can BUY (homemade is the actual best) is from Letena. Hands down. Order take out every Friday. Grab sambusas and chai and espresso for Brunches. <3

I can’t say enough good things about Letena. The food, the customer service, the atmosphere are all incredible. Every time I walk in I’m welcomed so warmly and made to feel right at home. It’s the first place I’ll take friends visiting the area and the food has never ever disappointed. Truly cannot recommend it enough!

Delicious, healthy and fresh food combined with warm and attentive service. The veggie sampler, Letena salad and shiro wot are my go-tos but the whole menu is a tour de force!  The takeout packaging allows for easy transport home. I was so glad when Letena reopened after being closed for the first months of quarantine—the staff always goes above and beyond, and ordering from here is always a bright spot after home cooked meals during the week!

Amazing food that is always fresh, well-seasoned and healthy!  Highly recommend the take-out for individual or large meals. Veggie sides are all delicious, especially the carrot wot!  The meat stews, tibs and fish are also fantastic.  They have the best takeout packaging— everything wrapped with love and care!  Pickup is easy and almost contactless.

My favorite restaurant! Order the red lentils (yemisir wot) or the chef’s signature tibs and you won’t be disappointed! I had cravings while they were temporarily closed during quarantine. I’m so glad they’re open again for take out 😁
I went there almost religiously when I used to live in dc. One of, if not the best ethiopian restaurant in the area taste and portion wise. Very clean too
Ambience is nice and they serve The best veggie platter.

By far the best restaurant I’ve gone to in a long time. The food was superb, the staff was super friendly, the atmosphere is great, and portions are fantastic for what you pay. I’ve been recommending it to everyone in that area and can’t wait to go back!

This place is phenomenal! As an Ethiopian myself, this food tasted authentic and delicious. For the price you get a a lot of food and a vegetable side which isn't common among Ethiopian restaurants in DC. This is up there with my favourite Ethiopian restaurants in America
I enjoyed every thing. Customer service was Superb. I can't eat  Hot peppers and too Spicy food. She brought me some beef. I am quite sure I will return or for Delivery.

Letena Ethiopian Restaurant has tasty Ethiopian dishes. Not DC's best, but definitely a higher-end place. Great selection of Ethiopian lagers. Good multi-dish sampler platters that are large enough to share with company.
Awesome
The food came out salty. We did give them feedback but nothing was done about it. Otherwise, the food was good-ish (because of too much salt). The atmosphere is great! Drinks were meh.

This was one of my favorite dining experiences in recent times :) We had a reservation, and they gave us this really nice corner table. We were always greeted with happy faces. The restaurant is just beautiful with art that really appealed to me. By the windows, they had jars of lentils too!  The injera itself was great! We never had to ask for more, they were waiting to offer us more. They accidentally gave us the collard greens instead of the carrot wot but they were happy to get us a side of that as well. Our favorites were the misir wot and the mushroom wot.  We not only felt welcomed here, we felt loved. Thank you so much!
Great food and service! Must go in the neighborhood
Excellent food! Kind, warm staff. Get the lamb stew and the vegetable sampler!
Great Ethiopian food! Will definitely be coming back for more

I caveat this review by admitting my bias in loving Ethiopian/Eritrean/East African cuisine. I've been lucky enough to call home some of the cities with the most dense populations of East Africans in the US; because of that, I've been privileged enough to know and appreciate the flavors of this cultural cuisine. So of course, I'm going to love it here; I knew that before I ever walked in.  That all said, Letena blew away my every expectation.  The food was more expensive and I received less of it than I have at any other Ethiopian place I've ever been too (not a tremendous, but a notable difference). That said the quality of meal was extraordinary; though the menu is familiar, the taste was somehow more complex and, simply, more delicious than any other Ehtiopoan food I've ever had. That is to say that any difference in price was entirely worthwhile. Furthermore, they provide this improved quality of food without compromising on the hospitality that I so deeply associate with Ethiopian cafes and restaurants - seeing that my injera was running low towards the end of my meal, the owner asked if he could bring me an additional piece and did so without charging me.  After I finished my meal, I called my significant other just to brag about how good my food was. I can't recall ever doing that for another restaurant; but I also can't recall too many other restaurants for which I enjoyed the experiences of eating like at Letena.
My food was delicious.
It was a nice relaxing spot for family and friends gathering, We had our New Year's get together.
Love it food, service, atmosphere all wonderful 😊😊😊😍😍😍
Excellent interior design and very good food + great customer service! A must see place!

This place has really stepped it up! It is the taste of home when you think of Homecooknig! Customer family; I first thought "Customer Friendly", but they go deeper than that. Give it a try, you wont be disappointed.
Excellent food! We had the bruschetta, veggie sampler, and a side of doro wat.  We ended the meal with their delicious tiramisu and Ethiopian tea. Will definitely be back!
Great food, great service

We went to Letena restaurant for the first time, such a disappointment for a beautiful layout restaurant.  If there was a star less than 1* I would have given it for the service. The server "Mamae" who is the worst from the time we step in, is unwelcoming and rude.  She didn't think we will pay for our food as well as service.  We feel like leaving the restaurant but eventually her colleagues took over.  We were so happy for not seeing her mad face again.  We as a customer need to be treated and served respectfully.  Sorry you lost us as a customer.
yummy
First time at an Ethiopian place. Carlos was an excellent server and the food was excellent! Will be back.

Excellent food and service. The GoredǴored appetizer and stew meat sampler were both very tasty. The dining room is nicely decorated, welcoming, and comfortable. A 3-minute walk from the Columbia Heights Metro station. Highly recommend.
Amazing & Relaxed atmosphere. The hosts look like they are waltzing to the rhythm of the mood, the ambience and the crowd. Good on you mate!
Got the Lega Tibs and it was hot, just like I like it!

Delicious food, impeccable service and cozy atmosphere combined for a great experience. For our very first visit to Letena, we were warmly greeted in and combined with the tasteful décor and cozy atmosphere we immediately felt comfortable. Although, new to Ethiopian cuisine, we enjoyed the tasting sampler and the variety of the menu. From starters to desserts, every dish was appetizing and flavorful. We left the restaurant wondering why we hadn’t been before but knowing that we will come back very soon

I ordered from Seamless and had a little trouble connecting with the delivery person, but she was gracious and understanding that I'm not a local. Can't wait to eat here again. I almost ate all the foods here. Very genuine Ethiopian food. They have option for vegan and non vegan. If you go as a group or two or one the place is amazing.The service is impressive. The design of the restaurant is fabulous. They have unisex toilet.

A favorite little local Ethiopian restaurant. While U Street has some of the more ritzy Ethiopian restaurants this is a much more casual place and they've got a nice selection of beer from Ethiopia as well.

We came here with a reservation for a large party and were overwhelmed by the quality of both the service and the food. There were so many wonderful menu options, both vegetarian and not. The staff were warm, inviting, and gave us excellent advice on things to try. Cannot recommend this place enough.
By far, the best Ethiopian restaurant on my list. Ambiance, food, customer service, everything was just great. This place is the real deal.
The best Ethiopian food in Dc!!!
Very nice , excellent service and food.
Very good food. Slightly pricey.

They have vegan options! Their veggie sampler is a great entree to share or try some of the very tasty options they have on their menu. Would highly recommend trying the lentils and mushrooms. The tables and chairs are comfortable and the decor is nice. A great place to come with friends or family to share a meal in a casual setting. Also, great service.

The food was adequate, but I was left with a sour taste due to the poor customer service received from our waitress. She was very aloof, inattentive, and made rather curt remarks throughout our entire visit. (We once inquired if a specific dish was available and she responded that the menu was on the table.) Also, many options were unavailable to include both food and drinks. I truly wished that I had not listened to the other reviews.

Spectacular lunch of beef, lamb, chicken and vegetarian options. All served on a large platter, it was so beautiful! Ethiopian bread, Ethiopian beer, and Ethiopian coffee just added to our pleasure. The food is so fresh, cooked to order with a ton of love. The owner is so interested in her guests having a wonderful experience and you feel it. Our granddaughter loved the chicken, salad and desserts. Thank you for the best lunch we had in DC during our visit!

This had become my favorite restaurant in DC. The ambiance is very cool, and more importantly, the food is just amazing. If you are a vegetarian in the city, this had to be in the top of your list. Every veggie dish is so flavorful and beautiful. And on top of all of this, it's cheap! $25 will get you a veggie platter big enough to share with probably 3 people. Highly recommend this place.

One of the best Ethiopian food I had. The lamb tip was great. Juicy, tender and a bit spicy. I recommend eating with the jalapeno. For the meat sampler, the chicken was a huge letdown. The tomato sauce is too overpowering. I prefer the injera over rice for my meal. The tea was full of spices, taste like chai to me. The place is small but cozy

Some of the best Ethiopian food I’ve ever experienced; appreciated how the stews were served in individual bowls and you could use the injera to scoop them, as I’d only been to places that ladle the stew directly onto the injera, making it hard to ration out. Delicious spiced tea, the cinnamon/cardamom/cloves were the perfect stomach-warmers for the food to come. Staff were wonderfully friendly and there was a birthday happening for which the entire restaurant chimed in. Some street parking but there’s parking garages next door for Target and other large department/grocery stores. Would gladly stop at every time I visit DC!

The food is delicious!

I ordered two samplers and skipped the carrot wot, but as a rule I love a six-dish sampler. Anyway, it's clunky for ordering but the food really is good!

I am a regular customer at Letena Resturant and they have a good customer service and serve Authentic Food. And frankly speaking they have the best Ethiopian Food much better than any Ethiopian Resturant all over America and always gave them 5 stars.

Great service and great food! Pretty small so there isnt much seating, but high quality delicious food. I always get the vegetarian sampler and every single one of their veggie options is great in my opinion. The salads are really good too. Great place!

Really liked this place. We were quick to get seated and served. My husband and I ordered the Shiro Wot, Yemisir Work, Kik and Fasolia. Our salads were the Beet & Potatoe Salad and the Letena Salad. My favorite was the Shiro Wot and he liked the Yemisir wot best. Most of the food is labeled as mild or hot (M or H), but I found the spicy items to be quite tame, which was fine with me. However, I do wish our selections were thicker. They were hard to grab with the injera. The injera is served room temperature, but I was okay with that. They gave an extra plate of injera for the two of us for no extra charge. Overall, great value for a meal. We split a single vegetarian sampler (no drinks) and our total was less than $20. I would recommend if you enjoy Ethiopian food, casual dining and no-fuss meals.
The food is really good and reasonably priced. I would definitely eat here again.

So Good! Our servers were extremely pleasant and friendly. The food was beyond expectations. Everything was so perfect. Super accommodating to allergies. I will definitely be returning. I am highly recommending this place to anyone trying to have an exquisite inexpensive sit down meal. 😎👍
Super quick service, friendly staff, and delicious food!

The carrot veggie dish was a surprising hit, and I don't think I could find a fresher avocado/broccoli dish (the Letena salad!) if I went and picked the veggies myself. Our server was warm and inviting, even though we were pretty unfamiliar with Ethiopian food as a whole. Looking forward to my next visit!

This place is a gem. Firstly, the food is fantastic. If you are not familiar with Ethiopian cuisine, one of the owners will be happy to show you how to eat it. You use the injera bread to grab your main dish and you twist it in the sauces and with your sides. Mmmm. We had the Chef's Signature Tibs (cubes of steak tenderloin sauteed in red onions and tasty seasoning) with some delicious vegetable sides made from chickpeas and lentils. And of course lots of injera which they kindly brought more of for free.  The place is family run and it feels like it. It feels as though you are being brought into someone's home to enjoy a delicious meal. They are very passionate about their food and do everything they can to make sure that you have a great experience.  They also serve excellent organic coffee to go and to stay. Traditional Ethiopian style or delicious lattes and cappuccinos. You can't go wrong either way. Finally, they have DC Brau on tap as well as a selection of wines and other beers. Everything is very reasonably priced for its size and quality (we made a whole lunch of our leftovers the next day!).
This place is amazing.  Fabulous and less greasy food than most Ethiopian restaurants.  Very reasonable prices.  Good coffee and spiced tea.  Lovely owner and staff.  Keep coming so it stays!
The food was great, and the service was even better. Quick, good quality Ethiopian food.
Attractive decor

Pretty dang good. Neat little place. Price is a bit elevated I think, but that's DC. I can't wait to try their coffee.

So yummy! Got the vegetable sampler later and it was plenty for two people. Love that they have a mitmita shaker next to the salt on the table.
Really great Ethiopian food-the service was attentive and kind, making sure we never ran out of injera. The veggie sampler was absolutely delicious and fed two people comfortably.
This is the best resturant so far. I randomly showed up and the people, the staff, the coffee aroma, the food was just perfect.
Hands down the best Ethiopian authentic food in the area!  The restaurant is well kept, clean and culturally decorated terrific ambiance. We had the beef tibs and veggie platter ……..Yummy!
Had the carrot wot. Delicious! Love the atmosphere and service too. They're about to start doing brunch (?!) Definitely recommend.
I had beef tips and mushrooms and it was so good! I enjoy Ethiopian food and this place was definitely no exception.
This is Simply the best Ethiopian restaurant in the country. Nice vibe, excellent food.
All of the meats were served cold, and the restaurant has a fast food atmosphere

I can't say enough about LeTena.  Having tried nearly every other Ethiopian restaurant in town, this is by far the best one.  They have the freshest salad choices; the veggie combo is perfectly spiced and generosly portioned.  Although not a big meat eater, I couldn't get enough of their tender Tibs (beef) with a special homemade sauce.  The staff is attentive and friendly.  With delicious food, free Wi-Fi and amazing coffee (must try their Counter Culture coffee), I find myself here fairly regularly.  Highly recommended.
My new favorite Ethiopian spot.  Excellent veggie dishes and the spicy beef dish was delicious.  This block on Park has some of the best food in the city.
Amazing food, nice local, and great people!
Great food and super friendly staff! Will definitely go back for more.

Really nice interior and delicious food, with some different options than I've seen at other Ethiopian restaurants around town. I love that you can build your own sampler platters. At $18 with tax, the veggie sampler was a good size for two hungry people.
Incredible food. Great atmosphere. Best Ethiopian food in the city.
